Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.62,0:00:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral! Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.01,0:00:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.84,0:00:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cant do this alone, help me please.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.26,0:00:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orbital brothers 5 and 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Push.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.64,0:00:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha- what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like we're not welcome here at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.86,0:00:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.72,0:00:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.04,0:00:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.63,0:00:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll keep them busy, you go on ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.18,0:00:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good way to 'bring it to 'em, class rep!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.35,0:01:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, please go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.51,0:01:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.46,0:01:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.37,0:01:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, I got you with that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.58,0:01:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come and get me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.41,0:01:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your life is less than half of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.33,0:01:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.06,0:01:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.88,0:01:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Now I have you in a stalemate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.67,0:01:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.55,0:01:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't protect myself from Kaito...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.01,0:02:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma, what would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.15,0:02:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn! Open! Open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.89,0:02:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.48,0:02:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You there, get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.34,0:02:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it continues like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.76,0:02:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.09,0:02:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The answer is obvious. You would 'bring it to 'em', Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.66,0:02:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Zubaba Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.05,0:02:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I send 1 card from my hand to the graveyard to special summon Fallen Cone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.81,0:02:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the magic card 'Drop Exchange'.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.38,0:03:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this card, I send 2 or more monsters from my side of the field to the graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.81,0:03:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to special summon a monster from my hand whose level equals the sum of the levels of those monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.76,0:03:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Level 3 Zubaba Knight and Level 1 Fallen Pinecone are sent to the graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.03,0:03:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I now special summon Kagetokage!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.90,0:03:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This monster cannot be normal summoned, it can only be special summoned from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.73,0:03:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two Level 4 monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.28,0:03:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overlay Gogogo Golem and Kagetokage!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With these 2 monsters I create the overlay network.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.17,0:03:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, No. 39, Aspiring Emperor Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.80,0:03:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hold on Astral! I'll save you for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.66,0:03:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? That's... Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.66,0:03:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other... who is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The contract with you will be continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.30,0:04:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.15,0:04:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who opens this door will gain a new power.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.77,0:04:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, in exchange he will lose his most important belonging.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.53,0:04:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are some interfering with the contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminate them with this power.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.07,0:04:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go through this door and gain the power of ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.65,0:04:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only when you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZeXal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.87,0:05:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they're all ingredients to color each day. \NDon't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.97,0:05:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.38,0:05:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth is, I was lonely. Until I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lied to myself that being alone was easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.23,0:05:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My favorite books and hobbies,\N they don't seem to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.63,0:05:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were the only one to nod in agreement with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.84,0:05:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness and sadness and anger and\N Do and Re and Mi and Fa and So and La and Ti and Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It doesn't work unless they're different,\N the harmony and the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.38,0:05:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one is exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.68,0:05:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because that's the reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.72,0:05:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the sounds are dissonant from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.15,0:05:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}don't give up on the strength that will get you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.39,0:06:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we reach the edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.46,0:06:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the view we see will be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.53,0:06:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.44,0:06:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're all ingredients to color each day.\N Don't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.54,0:06:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.61,0:06:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(222,390)}Numbers 24:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(350,466)}The soul of Xyz Summon! ZeXal!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've finally appeared, Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.83,0:06:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Aspiring Emperor Hope! Attack Photon Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.42,0:06:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Slash!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.51,0:06:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so predictable with your foolish skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:06:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Trap! Armored Back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a monster equipped with an equip card was destroyed, this card allows me to revive that monster and its equip card!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.37,0:07:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be revived, Photon Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So you revived Photon Leo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.28,0:07:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For Galaxy Eyes he needs 2 monsters with 2000 or more ATK.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.43,0:07:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.15,0:07:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZeXal is it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.33,0:07:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not tolerate this any longer! I will put an end to you now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.36,0:07:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.04,0:07:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orbital 7 at your service!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:08:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scrap!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.86,0:08:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be at my mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.69,0:08:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.70,0:08:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!? Will you come out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our turn for a while..!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be pulled out, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.98,0:08:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Photon Circler!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.22,0:08:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Circler has 1000 Attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.72,0:08:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It cannot be used to special summon Galaxy Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.82,0:08:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.93,0:08:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of the Photon Spear equipped to Photon Leo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster equipped with Photon Spear will count as 2 tributes for a special summon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.79,0:08:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behold my soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.17,0:09:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The incarnation of light, descend! Galaxy eyes Photon Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.30,0:09:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it finally appeared! Galaxy Eyes Photon Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.41,0:09:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Galaxy Eyes, attack Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.76,0:09:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Stream of Destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.82,0:09:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Galaxy Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.65,0:09:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Galaxy Eyes battles, it can remove both monsters from play!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your field is empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Photon Circler, direct attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.32,0:09:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the battle phase ends, Galaxy Eyes and Hope will return to the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.86,0:09:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And due to Galaxy-Eyes effect, Hope's overlay units will be absorbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.43,0:10:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For every Overlay Unit absorbed, Galaxy-Eyes' attack will increase by 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An attack of 4000!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.37,0:10:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the Quick-Play Magic from my hand, Galaxy-Strom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card destroys one Xyz Monster that doesn't have overlay units!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.78,0:10:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disappear, Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.62,0:10:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap activate, Xyz Reflect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.17,0:10:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a Xyz monster would be destroyed by a card effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That effect is negated, and it inflicts 800 damage to my opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.83,0:10:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.60,0:10:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph, not bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this level of damage is nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.09,0:10:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't your remember how powerless Hope is in front of Galaxy-Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet, I haven't finished {\i1}Bringing it to you{\i0} yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to show you the true form of Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.27,0:10:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my Life Points are below 1000, I can use Hope as material for,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.93,0:10:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos Xyz Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.86,0:11:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Chaos Numbers 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.64,0:11:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Power of Hope, the messenger who turns Chaos into light! Aspiring Emperor Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! A Chaos Numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.80,0:11:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe the Numbers actually have this kind of power...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.93,0:11:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Galaxy-Eyes still has the higher attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.36,0:11:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My target isn't Galaxy-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Aspiring Emperor Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.36,0:11:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one overlay unit, during this turn, Hope Ray's attack increases by 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.00,0:11:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Overlay Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.36,0:11:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, the attack of my opponent's monster decreases by 1000!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I choose Photon Circler!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Photon Circler!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.50,0:12:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope King Chaos Slash!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.16,0:12:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it over?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.60,0:12:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.62,0:12:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.70,0:12:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Photon Circler you destroyed has an effect, that halves the damage from when it was destroyed in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So he survived that attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.28,0:12:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card, and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.82,0:12:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the tables have turned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.15,0:12:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disappear in front of Galaxy-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.11,0:12:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Stream of Destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:13:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate my Trap! Clean Barrier-Clear Force-!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my opponent's monster declares an attack, that monster's attack returns to its original value!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Galaxy Eyes' original attack is 3000,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.63,0:13:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus the damage I receive is only 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the damage isn't fatal...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.98,0:13:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you only have 400 Life Points left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Hope showed its true form, it will end the same nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.31,0:13:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! The Emperor's Key!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaito...I cannot defeat this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, {\i1}Farewell...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.95,0:14:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What? Is that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.66,0:14:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Emperor's Key...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.77,0:14:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral! Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.95,0:14:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.22,0:14:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral! Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.62,0:14:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now enter the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enter the gate and acquire your new power!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.98,0:14:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in exchange, you shall lose your most precious belonging!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.06,0:14:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have that conviction?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.25,0:14:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ASTRAL!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.82,0:15:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma! Yuma, is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.70,0:15:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.53,0:15:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has the duel already started?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.98,0:15:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma, unfortunately my life points are already close to zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, just you wait! I'll come to your side!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.15,0:15:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait Yuma,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.74,0:15:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This world is different from yours
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.42,0:15:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't know, if it's safe for you to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.01,0:15:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Also, this is my battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.30,0:15:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral, you idiot, I won't let you carry everything on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.35,0:15:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I have the same ambitions!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.56,0:15:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the voice at the gate said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to acquire the power of ZeXal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.71,0:15:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But do you know what ZeXal is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I know? What is ZeXal?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.06,0:15:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's the miraculous power which saved my world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.81,0:16:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... in exchange for it, a person will lose his most precious belonging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get that power!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral, in order to save you, I don't care what price I have to pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'LL BRING IT TO 'EM!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.05,0:16:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma...I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.31,0:16:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,MY TURN!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...I construct the overlay network with myself and Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.43,0:16:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the moment for two seperate souls to crossover! Now the legendary power will come forth!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.59,0:16:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.57,0:16:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lets bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Change ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.34,0:17:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's...going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.27,0:17:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...what is? This is...me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.24,0:17:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my power!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.06,0:17:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.33,0:17:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This voice is from...Yuma Tsukumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.08,0:17:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fused yourselves together?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you only have 400 Life Points left!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.22,0:17:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-we can't do anything with that amount!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.85,0:17:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lets win this, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything depends on this draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.06,0:17:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The strongest duelist will inevitably always create his duels through the cards he draws!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.84,0:18:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Concentrate your power, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.98,0:18:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.28,0:18:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this! The Light! The Power! And combine yourselves on my right hand, to open the path toward Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.80,0:18:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shining Draw!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.05,0:18:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! ZeXal Weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.51,0:18:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unicorn King Spear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.00,0:18:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unicorn King becomes an equip card for Hope Ray,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.38,0:18:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And increase Hope Ray's Attack by 1900!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.85,0:18:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change! Unicorn Spear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Hope Ray's attack far exceeds Galaxy Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.19,0:18:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His attack is 4400!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:19:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Unicorn King Spear is equipped to Hope Ray, it negates the effects of an opponent's monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.22,0:19:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Galaxy-Eyes can't get away now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.97,0:19:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! ZeXal Weapon! Unicorn Slash!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.71,0:19:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate my Trap! Photon Shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I receive damage from a battle involving a photon monster, Photon Shock
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.73,0:19:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,deals the damage to both players!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.47,0:19:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Galaxy-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.08,0:19:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito... why are you collecting Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you acting like the underling of the devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.02,0:19:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.23,0:20:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to save my brother, I had to sell my soul to the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.44,0:20:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.76,0:20:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what happened... to both of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return this to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... Shark's soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.47,0:20:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've woken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.44,0:20:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.91,0:20:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems what Yuma said was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.10,0:20:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.05,0:20:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't look good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.50,0:20:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.99,0:20:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarise, just run for your lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.19,0:20:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.06,0:20:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Yuma is still...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.21,0:21:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's fine... believe in him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.53,0:21:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma... Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh... Wha- What is...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.88,0:21:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.55,0:21:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.87,0:21:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.19,0:21:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh... Hey, Kotori!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.89,0:21:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oooh, it's not just a 'hey', you're such an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.06,0:21:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still alive, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.93,0:21:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hahaha... of course I won't die... 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.10,0:21:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.04,0:21:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.66,0:22:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuma Tsukumo...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.98,0:22:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.38,0:22:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, there is something, I would like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.83,0:22:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Why are you so serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.19,0:22:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...what does that D on your T-shirt stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.06,0:22:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today's test is hard. I can't divide myself from pleasure and temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.13,0:22:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanna watch TV when I get home.\N The recent anime are fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.99,0:23:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In any case, this test is hard. \NLanguage, Math and English are especially bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.49,0:23:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm only average at science and social studies.\N The only thing I'm good at is P.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.67,0:23:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Wait up, Baby!) For who's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.37,0:23:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Is that, Baby!) ...am I remembering...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.81,0:23:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Just hold on, Baby!) ...the answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.37,0:23:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(What are we!? Baby!) ...they wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.04,0:23:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I write the correct answer on this paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in one year, in ten years, will anything change?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.52,0:23:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world I drew in the corner of my dreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.62,0:23:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}one day I will race through the open sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.40,0:23:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one can blame this heart of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.27,0:23:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing is really correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.75,0:23:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of a sudden the time in our world has stopped, and there are 3 suns in the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.10,0:24:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sun.. should exist only in our world... don't tell me... Kaito!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.10,0:24:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am glad you are fine, Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.10,0:24:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tch! Something is messing with my memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.65,0:24:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just...what is happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.80,0:24:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, we are reflecting the memory of our duels...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.38,0:24:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal! \NThe Time has Come! The Emergence of 3 Suns!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.63,0:24:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\b0}Kattobingu da ze, ore!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.65,0:24:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that D on Yuma's T-shirt stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.80,0:24:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Donkan{\i0}\N (Thickheaded)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.62,0:24:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Douheta{\i0}\N (Totally unskilled)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.56,0:24:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dosukeba {\i0}\N(Totally goofy)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.34,0:24:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Douaho{\i0}\N (Totally Stupid)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.21,0:24:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Doudemoii {\i0}\N(Not Worth Worrying About)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.18,0:24:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Doukechi{\i0}\N (Cheapskate)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.06,0:24:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dounimonaranai{\i0}\N (Helpless)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.28,0:24:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dounimozannen {\i0}\N(Helpless Disappointment)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.64,0:24:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Du- Duel, that is what the 'D' stands for!
